"&#xa0;\nWritten evidence from the Care Quality Commission (ACQ 02)&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nExecutive summary&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nStrategy implementation&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n2013/14\n2012/13\nRecurring budget (including \nHealthwatch\n England)\n£160m\n£153m\nTransformation budget\n£20m\n&#xa0;\nTotal revenue budget\n£180m\n£153m\nOf which:\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nBudgeted fee income\n£100m\n£93m\nGrant-in-aid\n80m\n£60m\n&#xa0;\nThe role of the Chief Inspectors&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;Single failure regime&#xa0;&#xa0;\nPutting people at the heart of what we do&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nCulture at CQC&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nUniversity Hospitals Morecambe Bay NHS Foundation Trust&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;Governance Structure&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nOctober 2013\n&#xa0;\nAnnex 1 – timeline for implementation of changes to CQC, including the roll out of the new regulatory model&#xa0;\nNovember 2013\n-\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nSignposting document setting out our early thinking on priorities for the regulation and inspection of GP and dental practices\n-\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nProposals on changes to the way CQC inspects mental health services, including how to integrate its regulatory work with it duties for the monitoring of people’s rights under the Mental Health Act\nEnd Dec 2013 \n-\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nA developing model for inspecting hospitals – completed inspections of 18 NHS Trusts and conducted three pilots on the new regulatory approach\n&#xa0;\nApril 2014 \n-\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nNew approach for hospitals started, with the first two waves of inspections concluded\n-\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nFirst wave pilot of mental health inspections concluded and second wave started\n-\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nFirst wave pilot of inspections in adult social care and primary care underway \n-\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nMajority of organisation restructured to support the development and implementation of new model \n-\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nReviewed governance and decision-making processes \n-\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nLaunch of Phase Two of the CQC Academy \n-\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nStakeholders engaged on principles of new approach and co-produced key changes \n-\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nLocal inspectors organised into inspectorates, with training in how to use new tools and methodologies\n&#xa0;\nApril 2015 \n-\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nNew approach for adult social care and primary care introduced \n-\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nEngaged on implementation on new approaches \n&#xa0;\nJanuary 2016 \n-\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nRolling programme of NHS inspections \n-\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nAll NHS and independent acute hospitals will have received a rating \n&#xa0;\nApril 2016 \n-\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nEmbedded differentiated frameworks across regulated sectors \n-\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nRatings published for all NHS and social care services \n-\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nAcademy offering qualifications \n-\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nPatient and professional groups engaged and involved in regulatory approaches\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n The performance targets for 2012/13 were set out in CQC’s Business Plan for 2012/13 which can be found: http://www.cqc.org.uk/sites/default/files/media/documents/cqc_business_plan_2012-13_final.pdf\n http://www.cqc.org.uk/sites/default/files/media/documents/20130918_cqc_statement_2013_final_tagged_sent_to_web.pdf\n"